File: Finance Minister Tito Mboweni's emergency budget makes provision for COVID-19 relief efforts.  JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Tito Mboweni is set to table an adjusted budget on 24 June. The emergency budget makes provision for COVID-19 relief efforts. WATCH: Finance minister speaks on R500bn relief package Treasury has published special adjustment budget guidelines which include deadlines for departments to make submissions on their adjustment budgets. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced last month that government would provide R500-billion in fiscal support to be directed to COVID-19 priorities. WATCH: Ramaphosa addresses nation on COVID-19 economic measures Of this amount, R130-billion was to be reprioritised from the national budget, which was tabled in February this year. Treasury says other adjustments not included in this emergency budget will be tabled in the October Adjustment Budget. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.